{"title":"Smith makes it a family ride with 2 new youth MIPS helmets","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/01/smith-new-youth-mips-helmets/","date":1630507820000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div data-off-canvas-content=\"\"><main role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-270015\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><header></header><section itemprop=\"text\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01051524/20210531_SMITH_BIKE_JR_MW_3508.jpg\"><figure><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01051524/20210531_SMITH_BIKE_JR_MW_3508.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs%3Adevice%2Frscb28-1\" alt=\"New Smith Wilder Jr. MIPS helmet for youth\" loading=\"eager\" data-feature=\"1\" srcset=\"\" sizes=\"\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\"><figcaption>All photos c. Smith Optics</figcaption></figure></a><p>Smith recently introduced two new youth helmets to its cycling lineup. The Wilder Jr. and Zip Jr. helmets come with pro-level MIPS technology in a kid-sized package.</p><p>There’s a lot the two noggin shells have in common, but let’s talk about what sets each one apart.</p><h2>Wilder Jr. Youth MIPS Helmet: MTB ready</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:740x493/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" alt=\"New Smith Wilder Jr. MIPS helmet for youth\" width=\"1199\" height=\"799\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1199w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1199px) 100vw, 1199px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714.jpg?ezimgfmt=rs:740x493/rscb28/ng:webp/ngcb28\" ezoid=\"0.9660062937920357\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 1199w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714-297x198.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714-800x533.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714-120x80.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01050140/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_1145-e1630487846714-768x512.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb28 768w\"></a></p><p>The <a href=\"https://www.smithoptics.com/en_US/helmets-youth/WILDER-JR-MIPS-HELMET.html?dwvar_WILDER-JR-MIPS-HELMET_color=electricBlue\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Wilder Jr. MTB MIPS helmet</a> is a mini-iteration of Smith’s grown-up models. Safety features, fit customization, performance-driven comfort, and architecture. We’ve only seen pictures, but the integrated visor makes the Wilder Jr. look like it’s cut out for your wilder junior.</p><p>Technically, Smith’s ‘youth’ helmets come in one size. But the 270-degree VaporFit dial adjusts the fit precisely, so your kid won’t lose their lid&nbsp; — especially important for all those full sends that turn into halfsies mid-air. The visor even boasts built-in <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/05/eyewear-roundup-new-smith-shift-mag-highsight-glasses-have-built-in-mirror-tifosi-shutout-kids-glasses/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">eyewear</a> storage for those quick juice box breaks in the shade.</p><p>The Wilder Jr. MTB helmet with MIPS comes in alder green, black, electric blue, or pink.</p><h3><strong>Features and fit</strong></h3><ul><li>MIPS Brain Protection System</li><li>VaporFit dial adjustment system</li><li>AirEvac ventilation (21 fixed vents)</li><li>Performance lining</li><li>Low-profile single layer webbing chin straps</li><li>Lightweight construction (10 oz./270 g)</li><li>Compatible with Smith performance eyewear</li></ul><h2>Zip Jr. MIPS Youth Helmet: low key heavy-duty</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927.jpg\" alt=\"2021 Smith Zip Jr MIPS Bike Helmet\" width=\"1200\" height=\"801\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927-768x513.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927-800x534.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045550/20210618_SMITH_BIKE_JRS_2_MW_053-e1630487930927-768x513.jpg 768w\"></a></p><p>The <a href=\"https://www.smithoptics.com/en_US/helmets-youth/ZIP-JR-MIPS-HELMET.html?dwvar_ZIP-JR-MIPS-HELMET_color=highVizYellow\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Zip Jr. MIPS helmet</a> is the ultra-light all-arounder. As with all ‘youth’ sized Smith helmets, it’s available in youth small. However, the 270-degree adjustable VaporFit knob will, as with the Wilder Jr., cinch or loosen that fit to nth degrees.</p><p>The MIPS protection and strong but non-invasive webbing chin straps will come in handy when they bite off a little more trail than they can chew (which will probably happen — a lot).</p><h3><strong>Features and fit</strong></h3><ul><li>MIPS Brain Protection System</li><li>VaporFit dial adjustment system</li><li>AirEvac ventilation (21 fixed vents)</li><li>Performance lining</li><li>Low-profile single layer webbing chin straps</li><li>Lightweight construction (8 oz./240 g)</li><li>Compatible with Smith performance eyewear</li></ul><p>The Zip Jr. helmet with MIPS comes in black, high-viz yellow, lava red, and snorkel blue.</p><h2><strong>Options, pricing</strong></h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045717/20210531_SMITH_BIKE_JR_MW_2486-e1630487963369.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045717/20210531_SMITH_BIKE_JR_MW_2486-e1630487963369.jpg\" alt=\"Girl adjusts the quick-fit knob on a Smith Wilder Jr. youth cycling helmet\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb28 src ng ngcb28\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/01045717/20210531_SMITH_BIKE_JR_MW_2486-e1630487963369.jpg\"></a></p><p>Smith prices both the Wilder Jr. and Zip Jr. MIPS helmets at $75 MSRP.</p><p>Each Smith youth MIPS helmet comes with a lifetime warranty and a 30-day return guarantee. And, if you order directly from Smith, shipping is free. Check ’em out at <a href=\"https://www.smithoptics.com/en_US/helmets-youth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Smithoptics.com</a>.</p></section></article></main></div></div>","author":"Jilli Cluff","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3147beeefbc8e1907390ccd0b9d6e04a22341cc1822c91533c666adbd38969f4","category":"Cycling"}